@Reasoning
Accessor for the operand_size field, which records the byte width of
the operand. Every operand kind stores its width in the same slot at
offset 56, so this accessor is operand-type-agnostic. Backends use the
size to choose between byte/word/dword/qword encodings on x86-64 and to
emit appropriately sized loads and stores.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. NULL-guard the operand pointer.
2. Read operand_size at offset 56 and return it.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One load plus one compare. Inlinable.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
NULL-safe. No type discrimination is needed because operand_size is
defined for every operand kind.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_operand_size" that takes operand as Integer returns Integer:
