@Reasoning
Type-checked accessor for the base_register field of a memory operand.
Returning 0 on non-memory operands prevents the addressing-mode lowering
from misinterpreting a register operand's id slot as a memory-operand
base, which would silently produce invalid effective-address calculations
during instruction selection.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. NULL-guard the operand pointer.
2. Read operand_type at offset 0.
3. If the type is not OPERAND_TYPE_MEMORY, return 0.
4. Otherwise, read base_register at offset 24 and return it.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Two loads plus two compare-and-branches. Inlinable. Called for every
load/store/lea lowering.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
